# Who Am I?
I am a student at the University of Minnesota - Twin Cities in the Computer Science BA program. 

For the 2015-2016 academic year, I am serving as the Vice-Chair of the UMN chapter of the Institute of Electrical and Electronic Engineers.

I am also currently curating the (somewhat defunct) Alfred Project that I started early in high school. 

# Languages I Work In
C#, C++, Assembly (x86, y86), Java, VB.Net, Python, Ocaml

# Projects
## Alfred Project
  An old AI project that I developed early in high school to try and compete with Siri (a lone competitor in the market at the time). Link [here](http://zenbhang.github.io/alfredproject).
